<P>"How can one "make sure" that every pet class on one's raid has pet hold?&nbsp; The only way I can think other than believing what the person tells you is to either require all pet classes to have premium magelos or else pay for premium EQ Players oneself.&nbsp;"</P>
<P>You're a raidleader and you don't check up on the AAs and gear of problem players (having trouble doing their part well on a raid)?&nbsp; </P>
<P>You&nbsp; choose to lead raids without using premium eqplayers info?&nbsp; I love this tool to help figure out what is going wrong when something is going wrong.&nbsp; To evaluate apps who are new or may need some training, etc.</P>
<P>I got a heads up that one necro didn't know what he was doing when I checked on him on eqplayers, as he wasn't doing too well on raids, and was unable to solo (a necro...), and I found he'd spent many of his less-than-100 AAs on random stats, including strength, and wisdom (wisdom???), while not working his critting AAs, etc.&nbsp; He didn't know what he was doing as a necro at all.&nbsp; Obviously.</P>
<P>We tried to teach him and give some input since he didn't know what he was doing (we work with people if possible), and although in some cases training helps people and they take off and become good, in his case, he was unwilling to learn--too proud--so he's gone, our content is too hard for a necro who spends his AAs on wisdom first and won't take input, lol.</P>
<P>You have to figure out the exact reason for problems to solve them, that's reality.&nbsp; Especially raiding.&nbsp; Not using any info you have to do that seems odd.</P>
<P>Premium is cheap.</P>
				
