<P>As a recruiter, or until very recently, magelos (including AA) was required for application. AA and the like can be hidden on EQPlayers as well, and frequently are, when they are updated.</P>
<P>Yes the applicants could lie, however if pets start flying everywhere on AE's and the like it would very soon become apparent that the applicant did not use/have the AA, and so would be penalised for not having&nbsp;it. Naturally if found to be lying their application would have been in jeopardy, but that has never happened to me.</P>
<P>But a classic sign of non-compliance with pet control is pet flying off at an AE. Have this occur and you can tell your slacker to not summon his pet, with the half life of a pet these days going down faster than a High Elf not partaking of good loving for 2 centuries control isn't a big issue as the pets would likely be dead and the pet classes not bothering to summon another after the first few.</P>
<P>But lest we remind that this is a game after all not the Geheime Staatspolizei, if any pet class doesn't know how to control their pet you simply tell them not to summon. If they ignore that directive you kick them from the raid and instance. End of Story.</P>
				
